Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.59,0:56:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be funny when you get here you'll be funny and you'll be funny yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.73,0:56:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what does that exactly mean to do so you're trying to do this on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.32,0:56:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,path and all of a sudden if you're standing on the road you just have to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.01,0:56:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,listen you're just going to say this is not the right path you're not gonna do
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.96,0:56:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it and you're going to have to deal with it and you're gonna have to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.09,0:56:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,not subject to time or circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.25,0:56:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is intrinsically so and true forever through all time?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.44,0:56:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say that God is the creator of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.15,0:56:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is so under all circumstances for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.42,0:56:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that every hair on your head should be counted is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.69,0:56:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you believe it or not is different,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.98,0:56:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but the truth is not subject to circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.51,0:56:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just reconfirm that one because I like that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.73,0:57:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.88,0:57:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on your head should be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.69,0:57:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.23,0:57:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.26,0:57:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's risky to trust people who don't believe in God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.84,0:57:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because people who believe in God know they're accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.21,0:57:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Judgment day will arrive, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.69,0:57:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,People who don't believe in God, what's the consequences of lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.30,0:57:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.57,0:57:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If a person doesn't believe in God, why not lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.34,0:57:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You should lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.69,0:57:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There are whole cultures that tell you that you should lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.59,0:57:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't lie, you get beaten when you get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.23,0:57:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to tell the tourists that this is a genuine antique
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.40,0:57:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and get $50 for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.15,0:57:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's mass produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.03,0:57:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It costs them $1.50.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.98,0:57:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you don't convince them that it's a real antique and get $50,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.92,0:57:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you actually get beaten when you get home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.36,0:58:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's a different kind of a culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.21,0:58:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to God at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.05,0:58:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you can say and do anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.76,0:58:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't really trust on a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.55,0:58:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can trust their likelihood of their behaving a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.92,0:58:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the ultimate, you can't really trust
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.23,0:58:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you're not accountable to God for your behavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.67,0:58:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're only into pragmatic using others.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.05,0:58:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So Werner had a very interesting definition,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.48,0:58:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remembered it all those years.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.34,0:58:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget when Werner was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.88,0:58:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in the early 70s, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.67,0:58:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it early 70s?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.61,0:58:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,71, 72?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.46,0:58:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody did Est.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.86,0:58:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a great experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.15,0:58:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It got people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.21,0:58:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of Est was to get people over 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.65,0:59:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop giving alibis, to stop being fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.11,0:59:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and accept the fact that, yeah, you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.92,0:59:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you are a rotten father, or you're a bum teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.28,0:59:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.51,0:59:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop pretending you're a big star.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.61,0:59:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is so all the time everywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.71,0:59:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a statement that's independent of context
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.63,0:59:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and timing and sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.63,0:59:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth then brings up the subjective and experiential
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.30,0:59:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that's within versus that which is demonstrable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.19,0:59:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth can be an existent reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.30,0:59:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's subjective and not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.69,0:59:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the mystic is not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.40,0:59:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's confirmable by consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.71,0:59:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.26,0:59:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the subjective and the experiential
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.26,0:59:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is a whole different field of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.26,1:00:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,reality and truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.36,1:00:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from that which is demonstrable and linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.36,1:00:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings up paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.96,1:00:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People become confined to a certain stratosphere,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.71,1:00:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you might, a certain content, context rather,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.78,1:00:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they try to corral all their,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.67,1:00:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,their understandings of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.67,1:00:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They try to put it in a certain paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.67,1:00:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The pedestrian, materialistic reductionism,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.67,1:00:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which deals with provable content in the notorious sense,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.73,1:00:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which deals with content in the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.73,1:00:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is a paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.73,1:00:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And people become very disturbed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.73,1:00:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if you try to talk to them about more abstract concepts.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.73,1:00:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll say that's all, whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.21,1:01:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a job one time in a clinic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.21,1:01:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I covered for psychiatrists being gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.21,1:01:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I covered a clinic in Codwood Friday afternoons
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.21,1:01:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were short of doctors there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.21,1:01:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the guy who ran the place asked me where I lived,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.21,1:01:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, uh, it's Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.21,1:01:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, oh, all the woo-woos.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.63,1:01:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to be careful not to talk about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.55,1:01:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn't literal concrete.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.32,1:01:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He would think that I'm a woo-woo.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.65,1:01:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.65,1:01:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of woo-woos in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.05,1:01:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're always seeing flying saucers and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.92,1:01:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of woo-woos in Sedona, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.92,1:01:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.40,1:01:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll never forget his saying that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.40,1:01:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.40,1:01:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, woo-woos.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.40,1:01:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way he said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.40,1:02:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning not practical, not down to earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.59,1:02:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a certain paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.59,1:02:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a limitation of paradigm of what's possible
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.59,1:02:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.76,1:02:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to present some work right now to a group
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.76,1:02:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's probably pretty just Newtonian ordinary consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.76,1:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that entails comprehending quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.76,1:02:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.55,1:02:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is not in explaining it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.63,1:02:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is my understanding how would you present
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.67,1:02:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced quantum theory to somebody who is still Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.67,1:02:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in their thinking pattern.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.92,1:02:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because when we do consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.92,1:02:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no here and there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.92,1:02:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In the quantum, infinite quantum reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.92,1:02:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is identical with consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.92,1:02:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.09,1:02:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no here or there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.09,1:02:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no now or then.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.25,1:02:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no future or past.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.25,1:03:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,An infinite universe has no center.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.28,1:03:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no middle of everythingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.28,1:03:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no beginningness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.28,1:03:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no endingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.28,1:03:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no here and there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.28,1:03:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's then and now and no future.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.28,1:03:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And all time is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.76,1:03:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All time is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.01,1:03:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All places are here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.01,1:03:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody get that?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.40,1:03:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere, wherever you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.80,1:03:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the same as anybody else because
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.80,1:03:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,here I'm the center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.80,1:03:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in an infinite universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.80,1:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but here I'm also in the center of the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.80,1:03:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because an infinite universe has no center.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.90,1:03:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why consciousness calibration works.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.90,1:03:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're picking up essence,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.90,1:03:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and essence is not dependent on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.90,1:03:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,time, location, or causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.03,1:03:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.44,1:04:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing is you're reading the essence
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.51,1:04:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of a thing at a distance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.51,1:04:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At a distance, you're holding the concept
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.63,1:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I'm looking at right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.63,1:04:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I don't have to go from here to there,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.76,1:04:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can, because I've done it millions of times,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.76,1:04:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of times, I can just about guess
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.76,1:04:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what it's going to calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.80,1:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just guess because I've done it a lot of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.80,1:04:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm looking at calibrates over 200, 201, 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.96,1:04:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm looking at calibrates at 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.44,1:04:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is what I got when I looked at it,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.44,1:04:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the cement pillar.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.78,1:04:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body calibrates at 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.78,1:04:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so does nature, and so does planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.78,1:04:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget the divinity of planet Earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.15,1:04:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.15,1:04:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.17,1:04:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, oh, dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.92,1:05:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We should lay down human life to serve dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.55,1:05:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmentalists, burn up houses,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.51,1:05:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,kill people for the sake of dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.51,1:05:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.01,1:05:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dirt's 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.01,1:05:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not worth killing a rabbit for dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.71,1:05:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Rabbit calibrates harder than dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.76,1:05:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body, there's no point in worshipping that either.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.26,1:05:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body calibrates at exactly 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.23,1:05:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body calibrates from dust you arise
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.23,1:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and from dust you return.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.23,1:05:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in being a narcissistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.42,1:05:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,worshipping the human body and all its glory,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.96,1:06:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and all its glory.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.11,1:06:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to be dust in a few years.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.32,1:06:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Came from dust, baby, you're going back to dust,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.32,1:06:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so forget all that fancy stuff, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.40,1:06:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Your body is the same as cement, dirt,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.40,1:06:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,roots of weeds.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.32,1:06:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,200, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.76,1:06:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,200 is neutral on the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.76,1:06:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.98,1:06:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you make of it is up to you from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.98,1:06:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can plant flowers in it,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.98,1:06:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can dump refuse in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.07,1:06:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really respect for your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.59,1:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,not for the earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.59,1:06:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people think that humanity should be eliminated
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.59,1:06:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can return the earth to its pristine nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.69,1:06:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of environmentalists think that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.69,1:06:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Man should be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.69,1:07:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think PETA, the guy who founded that,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.69,1:07:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who's a woo-woo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.69,1:07:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a real woo-woo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.17,1:07:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectuals.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.17,1:07:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book, Intellectual Morons,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.17,1:07:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which I just love the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.17,1:07:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because it just gives you the details
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.17,1:07:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,on idiots that you know are idiots,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.17,1:07:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but you didn't know all the details of how the...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.17,1:07:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,PETA, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.32,1:07:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We should kill all humans,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.51,1:07:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,kill all humans so we can give the world back
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.84,1:07:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dinosaurs, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.80,1:07:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinosaurs like to eat people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.80,1:07:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There weren't many people around at the time of dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.80,1:07:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaurs ate them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.63,1:07:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,People are nummy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.65,1:07:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.07,1:07:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.07,1:07:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.07,1:07:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms decide what's right and wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.07,1:07:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and unfortunately are also used to define truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.07,1:08:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So a cultural norm is very much a propagandized politicalization
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.07,1:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore what's normal in one environment
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.61,1:08:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is not normal in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.86,1:08:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.86,1:08:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dictate, then, behaviors.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.86,1:08:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would pass as okay on a beach here
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.86,1:08:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,would get you arrested over in an Arabic country,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.86,1:08:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,put away, probably killed,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.86,1:08:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,stoned to death, actually.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.86,1:08:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You try that over there and you get put away.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.86,1:08:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The allegorical versus the literal,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.69,1:08:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which means the letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.69,1:08:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.69,1:08:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the most frequent,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.76,1:08:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,most frequent political tricks
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.76,1:08:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is to distort the spirit of the law
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.76,1:08:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,under the guise of being the letter of the law or vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.97,1:08:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.15,1:09:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, there are signs everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.26,1:09:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see anything suspicious, please report it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.96,1:09:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That instantly brought up, as was put into the design.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.96,1:09:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just see if that was a design.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.82,1:09:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a conscious design,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.82,1:09:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm holding in mind, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.65,1:09:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.43,1:09:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Five more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.38,1:09:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We have five more minutes of what?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.67,1:09:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She's always telling me the end of the world is at hand
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.18,1:09:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's always been wrong, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.18,1:09:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's going to end in five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.60,1:09:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.47,1:09:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,An evolved mind instantly spots fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.47,1:09:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take the flying M.M.s.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.47,1:09:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The flying M.M.s.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.47,1:09:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Flying M.M.s.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.47,1:09:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was complete deception
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.47,1:10:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from the origination.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.47,1:10:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.47,1:10:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all preset.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.47,1:10:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Care set up the legal reaction to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.81,1:10:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing was designed and advanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.81,1:10:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the thing with the integrious people
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.48,1:10:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is they tend to be naive.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.48,1:10:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not held together by truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.48,1:10:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then deviousness becomes a standard tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.48,1:10:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A standard tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.48,1:10:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You set these people up to imitate
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.48,1:10:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,what in history was a devastating experience
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.68,1:10:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.68,1:10:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You set them up to imitate
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.68,1:10:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know what the response will be.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.68,1:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Care already was set up to soothe the people
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.68,1:10:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.68,1:10:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,picture these guys as being dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.68,1:10:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitating it to the point of the seat belt extenders.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.68,1:10:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They weren't just wandering down the aisle saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.68,1:10:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, I need a seat belt extender, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.06,1:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,None of them were fat.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.52,1:11:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the weakness of America is this naiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.72,1:11:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't think in devious,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.72,1:11:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,diabolical terms.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.03,1:11:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't think how can I set this up
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.03,1:11:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to create a reaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.23,1:11:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that reaction,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.75,1:11:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't be able to ever finger a terrorist again
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.84,1:11:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because you'll always be racial profiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.52,1:11:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're all coming from a certain culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.52,1:11:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't say anything about any of them
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.73,1:11:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,without being sued.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.96,1:11:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the defenders came up on television the other night
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.96,1:11:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and said, yes,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.96,1:11:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the protection of a court of law.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.72,1:11:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never been sued, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.72,1:11:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to lose your house.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.72,1:11:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to lose your car.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.72,1:11:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's going to be arguments.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.72,1:11:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to end up with a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.32,1:11:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not whether you're going to win in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.32,1:11:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawyers get $300 an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.40,1:11:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We get billed $300 an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.15,1:12:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, can't you fax this guy
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.11,1:12:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell him, no, we can't do it within 30 days?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.11,1:12:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They do.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.11,1:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a bill for $80.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.35,1:12:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the idea of this new law
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.51,1:12:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was to keep you from being sued
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.51,1:12:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you don't get wiped out
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.51,1:12:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by being sued because you're reporting.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.76,1:12:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All the signs in the airports,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.76,1:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,they report anything suspicious, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.50,1:12:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a gun in your pocket,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.50,1:12:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is that suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.21,1:12:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there you see a naivete sets us up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.61,1:12:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can see goodness in itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.77,1:12:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to some degree,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.77,1:12:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's a certain downside
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.77,1:12:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in that if you just become going to denial
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.77,1:12:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because of your own good inclinations towards others.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.77,1:12:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to be spiritual doesn't mean to be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.28,1:13:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I'm telling you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.02,1:13:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To be stupid doesn't mean you got to be dumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.11,1:13:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.15,1:13:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be blind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.15,1:13:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.25,1:13:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be very bright and alert.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.25,1:13:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the more your consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.25,1:13:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you're willing to look at the downside of things
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.25,1:13:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and say to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.25,1:13:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hey, looks to me like a setup.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.25,1:13:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you yourself are integrous and honest
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.35,1:13:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to know what the truth is.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.35,1:13:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to make them wrong at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.35,1:13:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, I compliment them.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.35,1:13:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a beautiful piece of stage work.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.35,1:13:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful. Beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.05,1:13:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It also tells you how cunning what you're up against.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.05,1:13:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact, how they would respond,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.07,1:13:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the legalities, the counter suit.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.07,1:13:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're seeing was totally calculated in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.07,1:13:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Completely calculated in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.31,1:13:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm just saying not to be naive
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.63,1:13:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,just because you're spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.63,1:14:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people are spiritually going to denial and naivete.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.63,1:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're worried about the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.63,1:14:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that are never going to happen
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.63,1:14:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and saving the earth and all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.63,1:14:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we just wanted to use the artistic of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.17,1:14:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And talk about some of the things in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.17,1:14:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because spiritually evolved people and students
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.17,1:14:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,don't live in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.17,1:14:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't all live in an ashram someplace
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.35,1:14:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,detached from the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.35,1:14:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We all are subject every day to this pounding by the media
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.35,1:14:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the politicized media.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.35,1:14:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have, how do you become,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.35,1:14:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you stay in a spiritual alignment with truth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.35,1:14:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world that is not aligned with truth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.35,1:14:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is the problem of modern man.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.35,1:14:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the subject of the book I'm working on
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.35,1:14:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and finishing right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.35,1:14:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality and Modern Man.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.35,1:14:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll take a break, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.48,1:15:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, hurry, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.56,1:15:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, hurry, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.90,1:15:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've already revealed more than all the world
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.31,1:15:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has known throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.31,1:15:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is a good start for the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.15,1:15:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Questions arise in people's minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.40,1:15:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we'll have questions
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.64,1:15:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and answers this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.64,1:15:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there's anything really pressing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.02,1:15:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just put your hand up and we'll stop the locomotive
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.02,1:15:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to handle something pressing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.36,1:15:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pressing, pressing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.36,1:15:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that you think would be of interest to the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.36,1:15:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so where were we on our phantasmagoria?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.19,1:16:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a great aunt who used to call something
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.80,1:16:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that was wonderful a monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.80,1:16:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a Christmas present you got
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.23,1:16:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that's so big they had a blanket over it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.23,1:16:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like a tricycle or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.23,1:16:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd say, oh that's probably a monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.76,1:16:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Word she made up.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.76,1:16:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.14,1:16:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So our work is sort of a monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.84,1:16:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talked about paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.22,1:16:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's difficult to get people who are pedestrian
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.35,1:16:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in their thinking below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.35,1:16:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the abstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.35,1:16:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Abstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.35,1:16:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you can't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.43,1:16:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of debunkers are there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.43,1:16:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the home of debunkers.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.46,1:16:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're into Newtonian materialistic linearity.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.46,1:16:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And anything that goes beyond that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.52,1:17:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they consider fraudulent.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.52,1:17:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So they set out to debunk it, debunk it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.52,1:17:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been debunked all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.64,1:17:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Debunkers.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.64,1:17:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the great debunkers is actually a stage
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.76,1:17:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,magician, a stage magician.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.23,1:17:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course occasionally they are useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.23,1:17:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally they're useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.23,1:17:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that they aren't.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.39,1:17:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.39,1:17:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So things have to fall within a certain paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.43,1:17:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to be accepted as possibly real.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.43,1:17:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's pretty much set by your whole culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.43,1:17:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The culture in which you grew up.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.43,1:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The culture that we are currently bombarded with.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.60,1:17:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What is within the norms?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.60,1:17:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now consciousness calibration itself is not within cultural norms.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.63,1:17:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The world thinks in terms of linear local causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.01,1:17:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you can read the essence of something
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.01,1:18:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at a great distance
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.17,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is not within their paradigm of possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.17,1:18:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore you would expect criticisms to come from people
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.27,1:18:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,who are literal and pedestrian
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.59,1:18:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in their thinking because they're not capable of thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.59,1:18:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in abstract terminology.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.59,1:18:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They think in terms of content and not context, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.61,1:18:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you can read anything anywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.61,1:18:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thing that's mind-boggling about consciousness calibration
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.35,1:18:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you can know anything about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.35,1:18:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in time or space
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.35,1:18:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as you get permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.27,1:18:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tell people when you use it,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.27,1:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I always ask, I have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.51,1:18:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And occasionally you'll get a no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.51,1:18:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I do it silently all the time with Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.51,1:18:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so as not to take up the audience's time
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.51,1:18:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but I should verbalize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.85,1:18:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because occasionally you'll get a no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.85,1:19:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you can find out the reason for the no
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.78,1:19:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and other times you can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.78,1:19:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually it's very seldom we get a no
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.01,1:19:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but many people do get a no.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.01,1:19:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And one reason you get it is because of karmic reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.01,1:19:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason people below 200 can't get the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.01,1:19:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with this methodology
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.01,1:19:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if you follow truth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.19,1:19:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what you end up with is God.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.19,1:19:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God and truth are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.19,1:19:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're an atheist, you negate God
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.30,1:19:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're not able to do kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.52,1:19:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And some well-known professors
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.52,1:19:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who attack kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.52,1:19:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't figure out why do they
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.52,1:19:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he calibrates 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.52,1:19:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he calibrate 190?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.52,1:19:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.52,1:19:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So then I got why it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.52,1:19:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we quit using the term.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.90,1:19:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't do kinesiology anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.90,1:19:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We just do muscle testing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.35,1:19:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't like the term so I'll throw it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.76,1:20:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I only mentioned the term begin with
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.76,1:20:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,out of respect for the teacher in which
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.76,1:20:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,whose class I saw how it worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.76,1:20:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I instantly got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.76,1:20:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw it as local.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.76,1:20:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw it as non-local.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.76,1:20:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought I would honor him by that reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.76,1:20:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if they don't take it that way
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.76,1:20:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll win.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.76,1:20:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I need kinesiology like a hole in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.94,1:20:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology actually is muscle testing
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.94,1:20:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to diagnose physical conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.94,1:20:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by physical response.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.94,1:20:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we're using it in a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.94,1:20:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I ever brought the word in.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.94,1:20:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We've eliminated it from the reproduction
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.94,1:20:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the new books.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.94,1:20:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We just eliminate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.94,1:20:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If people don't like it, take it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.81,1:20:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't want to offend anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.89,1:20:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the human mind of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.85,1:21:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about hermeneutics of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.85,1:21:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention set.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.39,1:21:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't understand the content
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.39,1:21:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you add the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.39,1:21:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a certain thing legal and okay in the United States?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.39,1:21:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.39,1:21:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends are you at war or not at war.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.39,1:21:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain things went on during World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.39,1:21:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,After the war was over they were eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.39,1:21:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But they were necessary at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.39,1:21:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we did Werner's, Werner Erhard's definition
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.28,1:21:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which I always like.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.28,1:21:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,True all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.28,1:21:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the understanding depends on your brain physiology,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.28,1:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,indoctrination, and your paradigms of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.28,1:21:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which are a reflection of what's normal in your culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.82,1:21:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Allegorical versus literal.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.82,1:21:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Letter versus sphere of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.82,1:21:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave that example right before the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.82,1:21:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Current litigation, the current laws
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.82,1:22:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that are under argumentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.82,1:22:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Which to me, try to use the letter of the law
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.89,1:22:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to escape the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.89,1:22:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So very often the letter of the law
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.89,1:22:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is used to defeat the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.89,1:22:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the law,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.11,1:22:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,report anything suspicious in the airport,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.68,1:22:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite obvious to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.68,1:22:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.61,1:22:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fallacy of mixing levels
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.26,1:22:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is what is true at one level
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.26,1:22:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is not necessarily true at another.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.26,1:22:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And render unto Caesar that which is Caesar's.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.72,1:22:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And unto God which is God's
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.72,1:22:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of expressing the different levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.68,1:22:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we see spiritual error
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.68,1:22:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because they try to apply a spiritual dictum
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.68,1:22:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is appropriate in this context
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.68,1:22:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but not appropriate in another context.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.68,1:23:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallacy of mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.18,1:23:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.72,1:23:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallacy of mixing levels
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.23,1:23:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is the basis for a lot of spiritual error.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.23,1:23:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in New Ages
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.23,1:23:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when there is a lot of materialism.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.14,1:23:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Limitations of science,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.14,1:23:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we gave the example of junk science.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.14,1:23:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And how it becomes politicized,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.14,1:23:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes a whole big world enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.26,1:23:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And mass delusions and madness of crowds
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.26,1:23:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is the only way to explain that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.64,1:23:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People get carried away with grandiosity about it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.64,1:23:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course the money pours in.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.64,1:23:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You have festivals all over the world
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.80,1:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome something that doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.82,1:23:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a lot of TV coverage.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.82,1:23:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,People do anything to get a few moments on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.82,1:23:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.82,1:23:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Including lying through their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.82,1:24:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the distortion of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.23,1:24:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,rhetoric and sophistry
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.23,1:24:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,has been noted in ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.23,1:24:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.27,1:24:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,part of being an educated spiritual student
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.27,1:24:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I think is to have some
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.27,1:24:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at least superficial understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.27,1:24:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the philosophy of ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.27,1:24:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our culture is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.27,1:24:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a Greco-Judo-Christian.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.27,1:24:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And our emphasis on reason and rationality
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.27,1:24:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of that ancient tradition.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.27,1:24:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are whole cultures, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.36,1:24:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which are not,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.36,1:24:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we just presume everybody's like us.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.36,1:24:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There are whole cultures that forbid reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.43,1:24:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We say they're dumb and not reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.72,1:24:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They forbid reason and the basis is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.55,1:24:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that reason may interfere with faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.55,1:24:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start using reason
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.47,1:24:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on a lot of religious concepts
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.60,1:24:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you throw them out as not being reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.60,1:25:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So reason is seen as a jeopardy to faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.93,1:25:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now St. Thomas Aquinas,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.93,1:25:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who was a doctor of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.47,1:25:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,said the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.47,1:25:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That reason supports faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.69,1:25:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And he saw reason and faith supporting each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.02,1:25:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And it certainly,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.27,1:25:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you can create a very logical reason
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.92,1:25:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for divinity and the explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.92,1:25:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.92,1:25:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and its theory
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.46,1:25:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly supports divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.46,1:25:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,just intrinsically.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.46,1:25:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an infinite field of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.46,1:25:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all arises
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.46,1:25:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of emergence of potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.46,1:25:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the actuality,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.46,1:25:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what we've been lecturing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.46,1:25:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,since the first lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.72,1:25:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The things don't happen by cause,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.72,1:26:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a linear Newtonian causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.72,1:26:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But an infinite potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.93,1:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.93,1:26:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,when local conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.93,1:26:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't see creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.71,1:26:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't see evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.71,1:26:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the next lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.71,1:26:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.35,1:26:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So junk science prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.35,1:26:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Junk science prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.35,1:26:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's politically popular
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.35,1:26:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's profitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.35,1:26:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get a grant on anything anywhere
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.35,1:26:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because I know the prejudice
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.35,1:26:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I have to do is calibrate the review committee
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.35,1:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can get a grant to study anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.35,1:26:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what I do is I put the end result that they want
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.42,1:26:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.42,1:26:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a secondhand smoke will cause crib deaths,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.42,1:26:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,cause psoriasis in old people.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.77,1:26:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what I want to write,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.77,1:26:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get a grant for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.77,1:26:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't run your department
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.84,1:27:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or university without a grant.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.47,1:27:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't keep your position as a professor
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.47,1:27:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you write papers.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.47,1:27:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see how it's rigged.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.47,1:27:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to write papers,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.47,1:27:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to get a grant.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.47,1:27:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To get a grant,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.47,1:27:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to write something politically pleasing
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.47,1:27:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to get the money,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.47,1:27:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so you tell them what they want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.07,1:27:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The distortion of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.64,1:27:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's said we've already had a whole lecture on relativism
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.64,1:27:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and its expression as rhetoric and sophistry.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.64,1:27:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And why it contributes so heavily
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.27,1:27:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to the decline of current academia.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.27,1:27:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.61,1:27:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody argued with me in a previous lecture about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.61,1:27:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the Duke University incident.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.61,1:27:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Duke University incident.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.84,1:27:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Three innocent men, proven innocent by DNA.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.97,1:27:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A faculty of 87 members signed a denunciation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.06,1:28:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of these three men.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.06,1:28:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Three young men, convicting them in advance,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.84,1:28:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even though the DNA layer proved them
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.11,1:28:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not only innocent but impossible
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.11,1:28:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for them to have been the ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.11,1:28:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's bad enough that that condemnation
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.76,1:28:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was racist and sexist.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.76,1:28:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's calibrate the Duke University 87 professors.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.78,1:28:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate over 120, 140, 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.94,1:28:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.94,1:28:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,People would dispute with me
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.23,1:28:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,whether academia has fallen.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.23,1:28:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire Duke...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.40,1:28:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,135.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.07,1:28:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Duke University faculty
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.07,1:28:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all signed their names for posterity,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.07,1:28:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.32,1:28:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, after the three gentlemen
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.86,1:28:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,were proven innocent via DNA,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.93,1:29:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the guy who first prosecuted them
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.64,1:29:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought was gonna get defrocked.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.64,1:29:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, God knows what'll come of it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.64,1:29:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Having been proven wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.85,1:29:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,did the Duke faculty retract?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.05,1:29:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.76,1:29:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only dishonest to begin with and warped,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.46,1:29:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but totally lacking in integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.46,1:29:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As an academic, if I made a mistake,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.46,1:29:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing I'm gonna tell you,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.46,1:29:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you it's a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.46,1:29:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like I'm telling you this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.46,1:29:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I never used the word kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.46,1:29:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It throws people in the wrong direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.52,1:29:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So why not admit a mistake, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.31,1:29:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,carried away by the enthusiasm
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.31,1:29:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fun of making people wrong, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.31,1:29:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all that sexism in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.31,1:29:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor black girl. Poor black girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.31,1:29:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Abused by these rich white boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.42,1:29:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They just jumped on that wagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.42,1:29:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so tempting.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.42,1:29:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta condemn these bad...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.42,1:29:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it isn't, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.44,1:29:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,making a mistake is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.44,1:30:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the poor judgment of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.44,1:30:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But not retracting it later.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.44,1:30:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, they have not retracted it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.55,1:30:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So we got what the condemnation calibrated, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.55,1:30:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The failure to retract.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.55,1:30:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The failure to retract that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.80,1:30:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 90, 95.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.02,1:30:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To say it in the first place is 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.63,1:30:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To not retract it is 95.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.63,1:30:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the commandments, one of the Ten Commandments,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.22,1:30:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which is enough to make every politician shudder,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.96,1:30:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is to bear false witness against your brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.43,1:30:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To bear false witness
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.53,1:30:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is breaking one of the Ten Commandments.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.53,1:30:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think people should just break
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.56,1:30:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the Ten Commandments willy-nilly
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.56,1:30:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then consider themselves politically superior
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.56,1:30:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that they've done so, or lead, or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.14,1:31:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why academia has gone down.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.42,1:31:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a typical example, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.42,1:31:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But the politicalization of just about everything
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.06,1:31:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,insinuates itself into such things as...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.06,1:31:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call it? Radical math now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.06,1:31:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't add up two things.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.06,1:31:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Two plus two plus two.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.06,1:31:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You add up two starving Africans.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.40,1:31:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Two starving African white or dark ladies.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.40,1:31:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you come up with social injustice.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.18,1:31:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What the mentally impaired don't get
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.35,1:31:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is that this is an unjust world.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.11,1:31:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all born unequal.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.11,1:31:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not two people in here that are equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.06,1:31:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born tall and handsome.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.06,1:31:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's short guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.88,1:32:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are born rich.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.88,1:32:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to come up to school in a Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.88,1:32:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a little old used car,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.88,1:32:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd tell my dad,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.88,1:32:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,drop me off in the block away.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.88,1:32:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids are all going to jeer at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.68,1:32:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have any money,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.27,1:32:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so my grandmother knit me sweaters.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.31,1:32:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what they did?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.31,1:32:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd grab the back of your sweater
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.31,1:32:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and look to see if there was a lapel there,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.31,1:32:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, oh, his mother made it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.34,1:32:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So nowadays a handmade sweater costs you a couple hundred.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.85,1:32:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And a machine made one.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.85,1:32:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But in those days the status was
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.01,1:32:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing in this world is created equal, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.01,1:32:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't chop all the tall people off at the legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.07,1:32:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the war in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.07,1:32:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bantu against the Watussis?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.30,1:32:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Bantu that were the midges,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.30,1:32:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the small ones, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.30,1:33:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They cut the Watussis' legs off
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.30,1:33:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so they'd be the same height.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.77,1:33:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.51,1:33:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the far left politically doesn't get
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.51,1:33:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we are created equal,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.51,1:33:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all unequal,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.51,1:33:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's not anybody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.51,1:33:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.72,1:33:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to make it somebody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.72,1:33:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to create a finger.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.72,1:33:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to find what is the basis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.72,1:33:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of what can be corrected,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.72,1:33:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and you correct it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.72,1:33:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You correct it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.72,1:33:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are born with very high IQs,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.72,1:33:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and other people are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.72,1:33:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the far left does not like
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.72,1:33:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole subject of IQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.10,1:33:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Some kids should follow an academic road
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.10,1:33:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and others should follow a vocational road.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.71,1:33:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.51,1:33:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be a well-to-do machinist
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.67,1:33:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,than a broke college dropout.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.67,1:33:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The last time I had something made
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.07,1:33:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by a machinist in Flagstaff,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.07,1:33:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it cost me a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.56,1:33:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted a couple of four-inch bearings
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.56,1:34:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,made for a great big waterwheel.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.56,1:34:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to have them special made.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.56,1:34:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.56,1:34:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,machinists make plenty of money.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.94,1:34:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't buy it at Walmart,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.94,1:34:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,don't get a machinist.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.46,1:34:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so what is truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.28,1:34:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is subject to programming
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.28,1:34:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.28,1:34:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The hermeneutics of abstraction,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.47,1:34:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's limited by attention set.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.60,1:34:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about the letter
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.38,1:34:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,versus the spirit of the law,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.38,1:34:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the fallacy of mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.38,1:34:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See, what is truth in one paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.38,1:34:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is not true in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.38,1:34:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's fair and equal in one sub-level of society
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.40,1:34:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is not fair and equal in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.40,1:34:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just sort people
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.40,1:34:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,according to race, sex, age,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.40,1:34:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,gender and all that kind of stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.43,1:34:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.53,1:34:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we talked about junk science
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.53,1:34:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and its popularization.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.53,1:34:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very big payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.72,1:35:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Distortion of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.72,1:35:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we already covered with the whole lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.72,1:35:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And as compared to absolutism,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.76,1:35:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got a kick out of some critic
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.76,1:35:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that wrote something about to warn them,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.76,1:35:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,warn them,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.76,1:35:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about the books I write,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.76,1:35:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,warning,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.76,1:35:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you're warned in advance
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.76,1:35:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.80,1:35:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Warning, he's an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.80,1:35:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A bad word.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.80,1:35:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A bad word means you don't,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.39,1:35:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not run by relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.39,1:35:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It means the truth is not just what you think it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.39,1:35:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it opposes the narcissistic position
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.50,1:35:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that if I think it or believe it,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.50,1:35:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it must be true.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.76,1:35:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it denies the existence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.76,1:35:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Which of course is the whole basis of absolutism.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.85,1:35:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there is an absolute scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.85,1:35:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.85,1:35:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels of consciousness are absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.85,1:35:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They absolutely go from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.85,1:36:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And they absolutely calibrate God at infinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.07,1:36:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough to boil the blood of any relativist.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.07,1:36:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.07,1:36:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How many slides do we have on truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.43,1:36:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't lie to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.68,1:36:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How many?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.68,1:36:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.60,1:36:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.60,1:36:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That tells me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.23,1:36:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
